    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 140\u00b0C/ 120\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 1 and boil a kettle</p><p>Trim and finely slice your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>and chop your <strong>chives </strong>finely, then peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 750ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-and-chive-risotto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, roughly tear and crumble both your <strong>flat white</strong> and<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong> directly into the pan</p><p>Cook over a high heat for 3-5 min or until starting to brown and caramelise \u2013 these are your <strong>caramelised mushrooms</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-and-chive-risotto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the<strong> caramelised</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray and put in the oven to keep warm</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat and add the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped chives</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) with a knob of<strong> butter</strong></p><p>Cook for 30 secs or until softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-and-chive-risotto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>arborio rice</strong> and<strong> chopped garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the butter</p><p>Add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until it's evaporated</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-and-chive-risotto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 1/3 of the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and stir continuously with a wooden spoon until it has absorbed</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-and-chive-risotto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-and-chive-risotto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, remove the <strong>risotto</strong> from the heat and stir in the <strong>grated cheese </strong>and<strong> clotted cream</strong></p><p>Remove the <strong>caramelised mushrooms </strong>from the oven and add <strong>half</strong> to the pan (save the other half for garnish!) and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy mushroom & chive risotto</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of boiled water if your risotto is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mushroom-and-chive-risotto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy mushroom & chive risotto</strong> topped with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>caramelised</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong></p><p>Garnish with a sprinkle of the <strong>remaining chopped</strong> <strong>chives</strong> and season with a good grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
